---
title: "Buyer — Representative CRT  |  Readable"
---
flowchart TB

  %% ======================================================================
  %% Buyer_CRT_Readable.mmd
  %% ======================================================================
  %% Built to the same standard as Broker_CRT_Readable and
  %% Seller_CRT_Readable: explicit IF/THEN chain, no synthesized trunk,
  %% wall statements in first person, inferred links shown separately
  %% (dashed), provenance in invisible comments at the end. The Cloud
  %% below was not searched for — it fell out of tracing all 20 active
  %% Buyer UDEs and finding where the chain naturally converged.
  %%
  %% NODE STYLE KEY (same convention as Broker/Seller):
  %%   solid border  = a direct statement from the Wall
  %%   dashed border = an inferred connecting step, not itself a Wall UDE
  %%
  %% All 20 active Buyer UDEs placed. Unlike Seller, nothing required
  %% flagging as terminating at a Structural Reality instead of the
  %% Cloud — noted as an honest difference, not forced for symmetry.
  %% ======================================================================

  classDef obj   fill:#e8b84b,stroke:#7a5c14,color:#2a2620,font-weight:bold,stroke-width:2px,font-size:12px
  classDef need  fill:#3f6f5e,stroke:#a6d9c4,color:#fff,font-weight:bold,stroke-width:2px,font-size:12px
  classDef wall  fill:#e9dfc3,stroke:#52493a,color:#2a2620,font-size:11px
  classDef inferred fill:#e9dfc3,stroke:#8d8268,color:#2a2620,font-size:11px,stroke-dasharray:4 3
  classDef cloud fill:#2a1010,stroke:#e05b5b,color:#fff,font-weight:bold,stroke-width:2.5px,font-size:12px

  OBJ["OBJECTIVE\nFind and buy a property that's right for me,\nwith confidence in the price and the process"]:::obj

  N1["NEED\nI need to see everything available,\nso I don't miss the right property"]:::need
  N2["NEED\nI need one coherent, trustworthy source\nguiding me through the whole process"]:::need
  OBJ --> N1
  OBJ --> N2

  %% ── BRANCH 1: broad search ─────────────────────────────────────────
  BS1["I have to search across so many\ndifferent apps and sites just to\nsee what's available"]:::wall
  N1 --> BS1

  BS2["Every time I switch platforms, I have\nto start over — none of my history or\npreferences carry over"]:::wall
  BS3["The listings I see first aren't the best\nfit for me — they're just the ones someone\npaid to put on top"]:::wall
  BS1 --> BS2
  BS1 --> BS3

  STALE["Checking so many separate,\nuncoordinated places means some of\nwhat I see is stale or a poor match"]:::inferred
  BS2 --> STALE
  BS3 --> STALE

  BS4["I message about a property only to\nfind out it was sold or rented weeks ago"]:::wall
  BS5["I keep missing properties that would've\nbeen perfect for me — I just never\nsaw them in time"]:::wall
  STALE --> BS4
  STALE --> BS5

  DIY["I end up doing all the work of finding,\nchecking, and comparing everything myself"]:::inferred
  BS4 --> DIY
  BS5 --> DIY

  BS6["Searching eats up hours of my time, and\nI end up doing the same searches over\nand over"]:::wall
  BS7["Comparing my options means building my\nown spreadsheets and doing all the\nlegwork myself"]:::wall
  BS8["I can't easily put two properties\nside by side and compare them fairly"]:::wall
  DIY --> BS6
  DIY --> BS7
  DIY --> BS8

  %% ── BRANCH 2: trust one source ───────────────────────────────────────
  INCONSIST["Because different sources tell me\ndifferent things, I can't just settle\non trusting one"]:::inferred
  N2 --> INCONSIST

  TR1["One listing tells me one thing, another\ntells me something completely different —\nI can't tell which one to trust"]:::wall
  TR2["I have no easy way to check if what a\nlisting says about a property is\nactually true"]:::wall
  TR3["I can't tell who's actually trustworthy —\nbrokers, portals, sellers all look the\nsame to me on paper"]:::wall
  INCONSIST --> TR1
  INCONSIST --> TR2
  INCONSIST --> TR3

  DOUBLECHECK["So I keep having to double-check\neverything myself, and feel like everyone\naround me already knows more than I do"]:::inferred
  TR1 --> DOUBLECHECK
  TR2 --> DOUBLECHECK
  TR3 --> DOUBLECHECK

  TR4["I feel like everyone else — the broker,\nthe seller — knows more about the\nmarket than I do"]:::wall
  TR5["I have to explain what I'm looking for\nover and over again to every new\nbroker or agent I talk to"]:::wall
  DOUBLECHECK --> TR4
  DOUBLECHECK --> TR5

  NOGUIDE["Even once I'm actually buying, there's no\none consistent party pulling it all\ntogether for me"]:::inferred
  TR5 --> NOGUIDE

  TR6["Everyone I talk to — brokers, banks,\nagents — tells me something different,\nand I don't know who to believe"]:::wall
  TR7["I have no real way of knowing if the\nasking price is fair or if I'm\nbeing overcharged"]:::wall
  TR8["Getting the broker, the bank, and the\nseller all on the same page keeps\ncausing delays I can't control"]:::wall
  TR9["I keep having to fill out the same forms\nand hand over the same documents at\nevery step of the purchase"]:::wall
  TR10["I don't understand my financing options\nuntil I'm already deep into the\nbuying process"]:::wall
  TR11["I'm never sure if I'll actually qualify\nfor the loan I need until very\nlate in the process"]:::wall
  TR12["Once the deal is in motion, I have no\nidea what stage it's actually at or\nwhat happens next"]:::wall
  NOGUIDE --> TR6
  NOGUIDE --> TR7
  NOGUIDE --> TR8
  NOGUIDE --> TR9
  NOGUIDE --> TR10
  NOGUIDE --> TR11
  NOGUIDE --> TR12

  %% ── CLOUD ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  CLOUD["CLOUD\nSee everything available   ⟷   One trustworthy, coordinated guide\n\nSearching broadly to avoid missing anything\nis exactly what produces the inconsistency\nand noise that stops me from confidently\nsettling on one guide. Settling on one guide\nrisks missing what exists outside their view.\nNeither path resolves the anxiety."]:::cloud

  BS6 --> CLOUD
  BS7 --> CLOUD
  BS8 --> CLOUD
  TR6 --> CLOUD
  TR7 --> CLOUD
  TR8 --> CLOUD
  TR9 --> CLOUD
  TR10 --> CLOUD
  TR11 --> CLOUD
  TR12 --> CLOUD

  %% ======================================================================
  %% TRACEABILITY (invisible when rendered — visible in source only)
  %%   U001→BS1  U011→BS2  U012→BS3  U006→BS4  U002→BS5
  %%   U003→BS6  U009→BS7  U123→BS8
  %%   U004→TR1  U005→TR2  U007→TR3  U008→TR4  U010→TR5
  %%   U124→TR6  U125→TR7  U126→TR8  U127→TR9  U128→TR10
  %%   U129→TR11  U130→TR12
  %%
  %% All 20 active Buyer UDEs placed. None flagged as unresolved.
  %%
  %% Assumptions sustaining the Cloud (identified AFTER the Cloud
  %% emerged from the chain, not before):
  %%   A1: The only way to make sure I don't miss the right property
  %%       is to check as many different sources as I can myself.
  %%   A2: If I settle on just one broker/source to trust and
  %%       coordinate everything, I risk missing properties or deals
  %%       that exist outside what that one source shows me.
  %% ======================================================================
